In v. 40 he says that upwards of seven years had passed since he became intimate with Maecenas; add to that the nine months that el apsed between his first introduction and his recall (S. i. 6. 61), and we bring the former event to the beginning of A.U.c. 716. How long he had been in possession of his Sabine estate wc cannot gather from this Satire ; but there is nothing in it to disturb the opinion that it was presented to him either in Amne. 721 or 722. He speaks familiarly of a country life no doubt, but one or two seasons there would give him a sufficient taste of that way of living to account for any expressions in this poem. · ·
